.TH "ABORTCONTROLLER.ABORT" "3JS" "September 17, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
AbortController.abort \- AbortController: abort() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]abort()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]AbortController\f[R] interface aborts an asynchronous operation
before it has completed.
This is able to abort fetch requests, the consumption of any response
bodies, or streams.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
abort()
abort(reason)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]reason\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The reason why the operation was aborted, which can be any JavaScript
value.
If not specified, the reason is set to \(lqAbortError\(rq
\f[CR]DOMException\f[R].
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
See the \f[CR]AbortSignal\f[R] page for usage examples.
.PP
You can find a \c
.UR https://github.com/mdn/dom-examples/tree/main/abort-api
full working example on GitHub
.UE \c
; you can also see it \c
.UR https://mdn.github.io/dom-examples/abort-api/
running live
.UE \c
\&.
.SH SEE ALSO
